wikipedia_page.main: Rory Warlow (13 April 1990) is an English sport shooter from Plymouth. At the 2012 Summer Olympics he competed in the Men's skeet, finishing in 16th place.At the 2014 Commonwealth Games, he won the bronze medal in the men's skeet, beating Cyprus's Andreas Chasikos to claim the medal.
